WEBVTT

00:00.701 --> 00:01.833
[sorrowful music]

00:01.902 --> 00:03.836
<i> - Adult mark (vo):</i>
<i> By the age of twelve,</i>

00:03.971 --> 00:06.304
<i> I had seen more corpses</i>
<i> than most coroners.</i>

00:06.340 --> 00:08.073
<i> My family didn't</i>
<i> throw parties.</i>

00:08.208 --> 00:10.575
<i> We didn't</i>
<i> go to restaurants.</i>

00:10.711 --> 00:11.243
<i> We socialized at wakes.</i>

00:12.780 --> 00:15.713
- Mary: It's a sin, alice,
but hardly a surprise.

00:15.750 --> 00:17.850
He was such a heavy smoker
and all.

00:17.985 --> 00:20.585
And all your second-hand smoke
didn't help either.

00:20.621 --> 00:21.587
[wailing]

00:21.722 --> 00:23.255
Oh, but, still, dear,
this is not on you.

00:23.257 --> 00:25.791
Oh, there, there.

00:25.860 --> 00:27.259
You just let it
all out, girl, yes.

00:27.328 --> 00:29.661
[weeping]

00:30.464 --> 00:31.262
- Hell of a man.

00:31.298 --> 00:33.598
We lost
a good one.

00:34.735 --> 00:36.334
<i> - My life was more wakes</i>
<i> than birthday parties</i>

00:36.336 --> 00:39.905
<i>And so I grew to love</i>
<i>the company that death brought.</i>

00:39.974 --> 00:42.140
- Hm, say one for me
while you're down there.

00:42.276 --> 00:44.576
<i> - There was only</i>
<i> one other person</i>

00:44.645 --> 00:46.211
<i> Who loved a wake</i>
<i> as much as me...</i>

00:46.280 --> 00:47.346
<i> My pop.</i>

00:47.481 --> 00:50.549
- Oh, sweet jesus,
what an ugly corpse!

00:50.618 --> 00:52.351
I've seen
christmas hamper turkeys

00:52.353 --> 00:53.819
That were
better-stuffed.

00:53.821 --> 00:55.354
- I wouldn't be caught dead
in that suit.

00:55.356 --> 00:57.556
- Mm-hm.

00:57.625 --> 00:59.057
Oh! Oh.

00:59.927 --> 01:00.258
I'm so sorry
for your loss.

01:01.862 --> 01:03.562
They did a really good job
on him.

01:03.564 --> 01:07.099
- 90 years old
and he died too young.

01:07.168 --> 01:09.902
- He looks
just like himself.

01:11.004 --> 01:13.038
A-and beautiful suit
you've got on him.

01:14.008 --> 01:15.574
Oh.

01:17.578 --> 01:19.111
Oh, it's all right.

01:20.014 --> 01:21.313
[teacup rattling]

01:23.551 --> 01:25.250
I can't tell whether
he's come to pay his respects,

01:25.319 --> 01:27.986
Or crawl in with the corpses.

01:29.056 --> 01:31.256
- Well, here comes
the honourable member,

01:31.325 --> 01:33.658
Sniffing around for votes.

01:33.694 --> 01:35.360
Tactless - I mean,
the body isn't even cold.

01:35.429 --> 01:37.195
- Well, the soup is, though.

01:37.231 --> 01:39.797
Shocking!
Agh!

01:42.937 --> 01:44.302
[emotional music]

01:54.414 --> 01:56.714
- I'll be right back.

01:58.119 --> 01:59.952
- Pst! Do you want these?

01:59.954 --> 02:00.886
- No.

02:00.955 --> 02:02.220
- Oh, really?

02:02.289 --> 02:03.889
Hm.

02:04.758 --> 02:06.124
[humming]

02:16.637 --> 02:17.302
- Paying your respects?

02:17.437 --> 02:19.438
Well,
[giggles]

02:19.440 --> 02:21.039
Came to the right undertaker.

02:21.075 --> 02:22.240
Mr. Anderson is the best.

02:22.276 --> 02:24.643
Top-notch.

02:24.645 --> 02:25.343
I'm here for my
great-uncle.

02:25.379 --> 02:28.180
Natural causes - no kids.

02:28.315 --> 02:29.547
Lived a good, clean life.

02:29.583 --> 02:31.015
No reason for tears.

02:36.323 --> 02:37.789
It's not scary.

02:37.925 --> 02:39.457
It's just like
a birthday party,

02:39.459 --> 02:41.226
But in reverse.

02:41.361 --> 02:43.695
Well, no presents,
just flowers.

02:44.365 --> 02:45.931
But you do get cards.

02:46.000 --> 02:48.466
When I go,
I want my obituary to read

02:48.502 --> 02:50.068
"lordy, lordy,
look who's dead."

02:51.138 --> 02:52.403
Maybe some plastic flamingos
on my grave?

02:52.439 --> 02:54.606
- You know, I could--
- I never seen

02:54.642 --> 02:56.074
A dead body before.

02:56.110 --> 02:57.209
<i> - Her first corpse!</i>

02:57.344 --> 02:58.610
<i> I couldn't believe my luck.</i>

02:58.612 --> 03:00.679
<i> I didn't play hockey;</i>
<i> I couldn't dance,</i>

03:00.748 --> 03:02.480
<i> But if there was one thing</i>
<i> I could do,</i>

03:02.516 --> 03:04.415
<i> It was work a funeral home.</i>

03:04.952 --> 03:06.251
- Allow me.

03:09.356 --> 03:11.290
[clattering glasses]

03:11.292 --> 03:12.958
[animated conversations]

03:13.027 --> 03:15.494
<i> This was more like a party</i>
<i> than a wake.</i>

03:15.629 --> 03:16.295
<i> The dead</i>
<i> I could handle.</i>

03:16.430 --> 03:18.930
<i> It was the living</i>
<i> I feared.</i>

03:19.466 --> 03:20.699
- Don't worry.

03:20.768 --> 03:23.167
I go to one of these
a week.

03:24.905 --> 03:27.472
<i> - I'd never seen</i>
<i> a young corpse before.</i>

03:27.474 --> 03:29.107
<i> A jean jacket?</i>

03:29.143 --> 03:30.308
<i> I didn't know caul's</i>
<i> had casual Friday.</i>

03:32.279 --> 03:34.479
<i> And the number seven</i>
<i> basic-model</i>
<i> plywood casket with no inlay</i>

03:34.481 --> 03:38.250
<i>And an off-white crepe interior</i>
<i>that seemed almost phoned in.</i>

03:38.385 --> 03:39.584
<i> I was surprised</i>
<i> they didn't just</i>

03:39.653 --> 03:42.520
<i> Throw him in a plastic bag</i>
<i> and toss him in the harbour.</i>

03:42.522 --> 03:44.522
- So, who do
we have here?

03:44.558 --> 03:45.323
- My uncle darby.

03:45.459 --> 03:48.126
He moved away
when I was young.

03:48.128 --> 03:50.061
- Natural causes, or...

03:50.196 --> 03:51.730
- He got
stabbed in jail.

03:51.732 --> 03:52.397
Everyone's gonna say he--

03:52.466 --> 03:54.599
- "passed away suddenly."

03:55.736 --> 03:57.803
That's how they'll write it up
in the paper.

03:58.372 --> 03:59.704
Don't worry.

04:00.540 --> 04:02.807
No one'll know.

04:11.051 --> 04:12.417
- Get up,
darby!

04:12.419 --> 04:14.353
You're not gonna let
a few old stabs

04:14.355 --> 04:15.887
Keep ya' down, are ya?

04:15.889 --> 04:17.723
- He's gone, boy,
let him go!

04:17.725 --> 04:19.424
- You let go of me!
What are you even doing here?

04:19.493 --> 04:20.692
You didn't even
like darby!

04:20.761 --> 04:22.394
- What are you
talking about?

04:22.396 --> 04:24.262
- Want to
get out of here?

04:24.397 --> 04:25.363
I know
a quiet little place

04:25.399 --> 04:27.766
Where we could
get a bite to eat.

04:28.636 --> 04:30.836
- Pop:
The woman over there.

04:30.971 --> 04:32.838
How long
and what cause?

04:32.973 --> 04:34.306
- Easy.

04:34.375 --> 04:35.973
She's got, like,
12 years, max.

04:36.010 --> 04:37.175
Heart attack.

04:37.244 --> 04:38.777
- Hm, okay, hm.

04:38.846 --> 04:41.379
- Buddy over there
with the long face

04:41.448 --> 04:43.181
Over by the mass cards?

04:43.183 --> 04:45.317
- His mother lived
'til she was 92.

04:45.386 --> 04:46.518
But he smokes a pipe.

04:46.520 --> 04:48.453
Put him down
for six years.

04:48.588 --> 04:50.522
Hm.

04:50.591 --> 04:52.157
Okay, missy:

04:52.292 --> 04:53.524
Your turn.

04:54.494 --> 04:55.494
All right,
that woman over there

04:55.629 --> 04:57.261
Kneeling by the casket.

04:58.365 --> 04:59.598
- Two years.
Hit by a truck?

04:59.600 --> 05:02.701
- Oh-ho!
She's a keeper!

05:02.836 --> 05:05.069
I like the way
she thinks. Ha.

05:05.105 --> 05:06.371
- Come on.

05:06.506 --> 05:08.239
I got us a ride
with alice.

05:09.276 --> 05:11.209
- There's always room
in a widow's car.

05:12.612 --> 05:14.912
- We're between cars.

05:18.618 --> 05:21.286
- Thanks for being
so sweet.

05:21.421 --> 05:22.687
I better
find my mom.

05:24.291 --> 05:25.657
<i> - And there it was:</i>

05:25.792 --> 05:26.658
<i> My first kiss.</i>

05:26.727 --> 05:28.426
<i> And it happened</i>
<i> in a funeral home,</i>

05:28.462 --> 05:31.696
<i> Which would be strange for</i>
<i> some,</i>
<i> but not for me.</i>

05:31.732 --> 05:33.765
<i> It was as natural</i>
<i> as if it had gone down</i>

05:33.801 --> 05:36.234
<i> At a garden party.</i>
<i> And why not?</i>

05:36.236 --> 05:38.370
<i> The legion made the sandwiches</i>
<i> for both events.</i>

05:38.505 --> 05:40.037
- Things are
looking up.

05:44.511 --> 05:45.911
♪♪

05:48.015 --> 05:50.182
<i> - The next day</i>
<i> she wasn't in school.</i>

05:50.184 --> 05:51.850
<i> I wanted to ask</i>
<i> where she was,</i>

05:51.852 --> 05:53.885
<i> But I didn't even</i>
<i> know her name!</i>

05:54.788 --> 05:56.320
- Attention,
children!

05:57.191 --> 05:58.790
Mr. Chafe is concerned

05:58.792 --> 06:00.925
That part of your education
is lacking.

06:00.961 --> 06:03.328
- I didn't mean for--
- oh, don't.

06:03.463 --> 06:06.131
You wanted it taught
and so it will be taught.

06:06.200 --> 06:06.664
By you.

06:06.700 --> 06:08.966
Take it away.

06:10.371 --> 06:11.736
- Huh.

06:15.675 --> 06:17.241
[giggling]

06:17.745 --> 06:20.278
- Children!

06:20.314 --> 06:21.880
Go ahead,
mr. Chafe.

06:21.882 --> 06:23.481
I expect to learn
a thing or two myself.

06:24.885 --> 06:25.450
[sighs]
[clears throat]

06:27.187 --> 06:29.821
- You're young men
and women now

06:29.857 --> 06:32.424
And your bodies
are going to start to change.

06:33.627 --> 06:35.660
The boys are going
to start to wear deodorant

06:35.729 --> 06:37.795
And the girls
are gonna start wearing...

06:38.499 --> 06:39.864
You know.

06:40.968 --> 06:41.700
There comes a time
in life--

06:41.702 --> 06:44.135
Yes, fox?

06:44.772 --> 06:45.703
- Do you mean sex?

06:45.739 --> 06:47.305
- Yes!
- No!

06:48.275 --> 06:50.308
I told you
if we taught reproduction

06:50.344 --> 06:52.543
It would devolve into
a conversation about...

06:53.080 --> 06:55.112
[gulp]
sex!

06:55.149 --> 06:56.581
<i> - I already knew</i>
<i> everything I needed to know</i>

06:56.716 --> 06:58.683
<i> About the birds</i>
<i> and the bees.</i>

06:58.719 --> 07:01.118
<i> I was in love.</i>

07:01.155 --> 07:02.787
[heated discussion
continues in background]

07:02.856 --> 07:04.689
- What's her name?
- Huh?

07:04.758 --> 07:05.490
- What's her name?

07:05.559 --> 07:07.793
- Feeling chatty?

07:07.928 --> 07:08.994
Why don't you
tell us

07:09.129 --> 07:11.062
The parts of the
reproductive system?

07:11.598 --> 07:14.132
See?

07:14.201 --> 07:15.433
[scoffs]

07:15.469 --> 07:17.869
Children are just too young
to learn about such things.

07:17.905 --> 07:20.272
- Womb, fallopian tubes,
ovaries.

07:20.274 --> 07:21.873
But you don't have
any of that, ritchie.

07:21.909 --> 07:23.675
You only got
a dicky bird.

07:23.677 --> 07:24.943
- [giggling]
- look what you started!

07:24.945 --> 07:28.346
- You're the one who asked
what a dicky-bird was, sister.

07:28.348 --> 07:30.949
Not a very appropriate question,
if you ask me.

07:32.519 --> 07:35.353
- I will see you
in your office after school.

07:37.357 --> 07:38.689
[mischievous music]

07:41.929 --> 07:43.461
- Get out your bibles.

07:43.964 --> 07:45.396
[groaning]

07:49.436 --> 07:50.735
♪♪

07:53.440 --> 07:54.739
- Dick:
Hello, neighbour!

07:54.741 --> 07:56.374
What a surprise.

07:56.410 --> 07:58.576
Need a cup of sugar
or you already sweet enough?

07:58.612 --> 07:59.644
- No, I need
a car, though.

07:59.646 --> 08:02.113
Sick of
bumming rides.

08:02.249 --> 08:03.782
How much are you
selling her for?

08:03.917 --> 08:04.716
How about a deal
for an old friend?

08:04.851 --> 08:07.652
- Oh, no, mary,
you don't want this one.

08:07.721 --> 08:09.620
Station told me
to get rid of her.

08:09.656 --> 08:11.055
Shocks are gone
and the brake pads

08:11.124 --> 08:11.856
Are as bald
as the tires.

08:11.925 --> 08:13.859
Besides,
mike would kill me.

08:13.994 --> 08:16.861
- Mike's not the one buying her,
though, is he?

08:16.897 --> 08:18.997
Now, you take me
for a test drive right now

08:19.132 --> 08:21.600
Or I'm going to go into that
station and tell mr. Butler

08:21.602 --> 08:24.769
That you're refusing to sell
his junk because you're sexist!

08:24.771 --> 08:26.337
[bright music]

08:36.817 --> 08:38.483
- You're not eating.

08:38.485 --> 08:39.684
- I'm not hungry.

08:39.819 --> 08:41.987
- You're in love
with the fox!

08:42.122 --> 08:43.688
- You crazy?
Why would you say that?

08:43.690 --> 08:45.890
- You must
like somebody.

08:45.959 --> 08:47.626
You look miserable
and she's the only girl

08:47.628 --> 08:48.893
That will
talk to us.

08:50.531 --> 08:51.896
- Okay.

08:51.965 --> 08:53.698
But promise
you won't say anything.

08:57.704 --> 08:59.237
(whispering)
I like what's-her-name.

08:59.306 --> 09:00.571
- Who?

09:00.607 --> 09:01.772
- That girl who
wasn't in class.

09:01.808 --> 09:03.308
- So, you like her,

09:03.310 --> 09:05.210
But you don't
even know her name?

09:05.345 --> 09:05.776
- Well...

09:07.180 --> 09:08.813
- Do you mind
if I ask fox out, then?

09:08.849 --> 09:10.181
- Are you nuts?

09:10.183 --> 09:11.616
You can't ask
fox out!

09:11.618 --> 09:12.684
- So, you do like her!

09:12.819 --> 09:14.185
You can't have
all the girls!

09:14.321 --> 09:16.654
Not what's-her-name
and fox!

09:16.690 --> 09:18.489
- Look at the
sucky babies!

09:19.993 --> 09:21.593
<i> - The dreaded</i>
<i> fox brothers.</i>

09:22.729 --> 09:23.795
<i> The only things that</i>
<i> differentiated them</i>

09:23.930 --> 09:25.797
<i>From one another was their ages</i>
<i>and their mothers.</i>

09:25.866 --> 09:29.200
- Oh, gross!
Japanese food.

09:29.236 --> 09:30.602
- I keep telling you:
I'm filipino.

09:30.737 --> 09:31.803
- Middle fox:
What'd you say?

09:31.938 --> 09:34.873
I don't speak
chinese!

09:34.875 --> 09:37.475
<i> - The foxes' inability</i>
<i> to properly bully ritchie</i>

09:37.544 --> 09:39.711
<i> Was a stunning indictment</i>
<i> of the catholic school</i>

09:39.846 --> 09:41.212
<i> Geography program.</i>

09:41.214 --> 09:41.913
- You want
your sandwich back, geek?

09:41.915 --> 09:44.281
- Not really.

09:44.318 --> 09:45.684
- Well, you're not
getting it!

09:45.686 --> 09:46.051
- Okay.

09:46.053 --> 09:47.852
- I hear

09:47.888 --> 09:50.021
You've got a crush
on my sister.

09:50.023 --> 09:51.423
- Who told you that?

09:51.558 --> 09:53.024
- Mr. Miyagi over there
just said it.

09:53.060 --> 09:53.658
- Mr. Miyagi
is japanese.

09:53.793 --> 09:55.794
- Shut up,
short-round!

09:55.929 --> 09:57.429
- Vietnamese.

09:58.765 --> 10:00.432
- Try anything
with my sister

10:00.567 --> 10:02.834
And I'll rip your nuts off,
feed 'em to your boyfriend,

10:02.836 --> 10:03.901
Tell him
they're chicken balls.

10:03.903 --> 10:05.971
- That's chinese!

10:06.106 --> 10:08.039
Besides, he's not
into your sister.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.974
He already told me
he likes somebody else.

10:10.043 --> 10:11.676
- Will you shut up?

10:14.514 --> 10:15.913
- You hear that?

10:15.915 --> 10:17.849
This little tool
doesn't love you anymore.

10:18.585 --> 10:19.050
Aw!

10:19.086 --> 10:21.185
- Heart burn!

10:22.489 --> 10:25.924
- Gary: Hey! What the hell?
What the hell are you doing?

10:25.926 --> 10:27.525
[melancholy music]

10:32.732 --> 10:33.931
- What?

10:33.967 --> 10:35.967
I got rid of them,
didn't I?

10:35.969 --> 10:37.802
- Dick: A little
to the right, mary.

10:37.937 --> 10:39.471
Look out!
To the left, now!

10:39.473 --> 10:41.272
- Oh, which is it?
Make up your bloody mind.

10:41.308 --> 10:42.807
- Driving
is like colouring;

10:42.809 --> 10:44.675
You have to
stay inside the lines.

10:44.711 --> 10:46.211
- Too much stuff
on here!

10:46.346 --> 10:48.146
[siren whoops]
[passing car honks]

10:48.215 --> 10:50.415
- You do have a license,
right?

10:50.484 --> 10:51.415
- Don't be so foolish!
Of course I do!

10:51.451 --> 10:54.352
I use it for the I.D.
To cash cheques.

10:54.487 --> 10:55.953
- Pull over to the side!
[horn honking]

10:56.023 --> 10:56.888
Oh, mother!
[tires squealing]

10:56.890 --> 10:59.157
[sigh]
[siren wailing]

10:59.292 --> 11:01.226
- Oh, how do I turn
this bloody siren off?

11:01.361 --> 11:01.892
It's got me all
distracted!

11:03.330 --> 11:03.961
- That's not
our siren.

11:03.997 --> 11:06.197
It's the cops.

11:07.100 --> 11:07.799
[brakes squealing]

11:07.801 --> 11:10.168
[groaning]

11:10.804 --> 11:12.436
[engines idling]

11:13.907 --> 11:16.240
Well, this steering
doesn't work!

11:16.276 --> 11:18.777
I'm not paying
full price for this!

11:18.779 --> 11:20.245
[phone ringing]

11:20.380 --> 11:21.780
- Good god!

11:21.782 --> 11:23.782
Who the hell is calling
the house at this hour?

11:23.917 --> 11:25.049
It's eight o'clock
at night!

11:25.118 --> 11:26.584
Mary!
Telephone!

11:27.320 --> 11:28.853
- Mike!
Telephone!

11:28.855 --> 11:30.522
[phone continues ringing]

11:30.524 --> 11:31.956
[rock music
through headphones]

11:33.293 --> 11:34.859
<i> - In our house, everyone</i>
<i> could hear your conversation</i>

11:34.861 --> 11:37.328
<i> Even if they</i>
<i> didn't want to.</i>

11:37.330 --> 11:38.730
<i> But they all</i>
<i> wanted to.</i>

11:38.865 --> 11:40.397
- Well, somebody
answer it!

11:43.737 --> 11:45.203
- Hello?

11:45.338 --> 11:47.072
<i> - My mother always</i>
<i> answered the phone</i>

11:47.207 --> 11:47.872
<i> In a mildly</i>
<i> english accent.</i>

11:48.007 --> 11:50.274
- Just one moment,
please.

11:51.144 --> 11:52.944
My god, it's a girl!
For mark!

11:53.079 --> 11:54.812
- Mike sr.: For mark?
- Pop: What?

11:54.948 --> 11:56.747
- Mike sr.: Good god,
what does she want?

11:56.783 --> 11:58.016
- How do you do?

11:58.151 --> 12:00.218
May I ask
who's telephoning?

12:01.154 --> 12:02.620
Some hussy
named tina.

12:02.756 --> 12:04.021
<i> - Tina!</i>

12:04.023 --> 12:05.556
<i> I knew her name!</i>

12:05.625 --> 12:08.026
<i>I finally had the missing piece</i>
<i>to the puzzle</i>

12:08.028 --> 12:09.561
<i> Of my 12-year-old heart.</i>

12:10.497 --> 12:12.263
- Can I please
have the phone?

12:16.703 --> 12:17.936
Hello?

12:18.071 --> 12:19.036
- Hi, it's me, tina.

12:19.072 --> 12:22.173
- Oh, hi, tina.

12:22.209 --> 12:24.142
- Tina? Tina who?
Who's tina.

12:24.144 --> 12:26.177
- Tina from the
funeral home.

12:27.147 --> 12:29.247
- Tina reardon?
[gasps]

12:29.316 --> 12:31.382
Her uncle
was stabbed in prison.

12:31.384 --> 12:33.184
Hard as nails,
that crowd!

12:34.321 --> 12:36.720
- Ask her if her mother
will do an interview

12:36.757 --> 12:37.989
About the murder.

12:38.124 --> 12:39.090
- Uh, how you doing?

12:39.092 --> 12:41.893
- I'm okay.
- Cool.

12:41.895 --> 12:43.194
- She's too hard
for you, mark!

12:43.230 --> 12:44.662
You'll get stabbed.

12:44.798 --> 12:46.330
<i> - Tina: Wasn't hard</i>
<i> to find your number.</i>

12:46.366 --> 12:48.066
<i> You're the only critch</i>
<i> on kenmount road.</i>

12:48.201 --> 12:50.535
- Only house, too.
- Cool.

12:50.537 --> 12:53.004
<i> - I had a nice time</i>
at the funeral home.

12:53.139 --> 12:55.273
You want to,
I don't know,

12:55.275 --> 12:56.974
<i> Do something</i>
<i> some time?</i>

12:57.010 --> 12:58.343
- Cool.

12:58.345 --> 13:00.811
- Oh, the boy is quite
the conversationalist.

13:00.847 --> 13:01.912
[pop chuckles]

13:01.948 --> 13:03.714
<i> - Ah, do you want to</i>
<i> go to the park tomorrow,</i>

13:03.784 --> 13:04.382
Around two?

13:04.517 --> 13:06.551
Meet you
by the swings.

13:06.553 --> 13:07.352
- Cool.

13:07.487 --> 13:09.420
- Tell her you think
she's pretty.

13:09.422 --> 13:11.822
- Ask her how many times
her uncle was stabbed.

13:11.858 --> 13:13.958
<i> - I wanted to tell her</i>
<i> that I'd never felt so alive</i>

13:14.027 --> 13:15.492
<i> In my young life</i>

13:15.529 --> 13:17.895
<i> And we would always have</i>
<i> the joyful sadness</i>

13:17.964 --> 13:19.497
<i> Of the funeral home.</i>

13:19.632 --> 13:20.998
- Tina,

13:21.835 --> 13:23.033
I...

13:23.436 --> 13:25.603
I...

13:25.605 --> 13:27.171
[cord snaps]

13:30.710 --> 13:32.076
[dial tone]

13:34.948 --> 13:37.381
No!
I don't have her number!

13:37.417 --> 13:39.049
- Well, you really
shagged that one up.

13:39.085 --> 13:41.219
[slams receiver down]

13:41.288 --> 13:42.887
- I'm going
to my room.

13:42.889 --> 13:45.122
Everyone ju-just
leave me alone!

13:45.158 --> 13:45.956
[slams phone down]

13:45.992 --> 13:48.359
[melancholy music]

13:50.997 --> 13:54.131
<i> - There's no better place</i>
<i> for a broken-hearted pre-teen</i>

13:54.167 --> 13:56.367
<i> Than his bedroom.</i>

13:56.403 --> 13:57.167
<i> A private sanctuary where--</i>

13:57.204 --> 13:59.470
- Pop: All right,
don't mind me.

13:59.506 --> 14:00.938
I know you want
to be alone.

14:01.007 --> 14:03.074
I'll be quiet
as a church mouse.

14:03.810 --> 14:04.942
Oof!

14:04.978 --> 14:06.210
Oh, ohh.

14:06.279 --> 14:07.011
My dogs are barking.

14:07.146 --> 14:09.446
[chuckles]
[sighs]

14:11.151 --> 14:13.450
Good night!
Hm, hm-hm-hm.

14:15.021 --> 14:16.587
[lighter strikes]

14:18.191 --> 14:19.723
[lighter down
on bedside table]

14:20.627 --> 14:21.959
[bed creaking]

14:23.163 --> 14:24.728
[pop coughing
non-stop]

14:28.034 --> 14:30.768
Oh, jesus...

14:30.837 --> 14:32.236
[coughing]

14:35.442 --> 14:37.175
I can't smoke
lying down anymore.

14:39.880 --> 14:41.112
I must be
getting old.

14:41.781 --> 14:43.047
[sniffling]

14:43.182 --> 14:44.114
[loud sigh]

14:44.150 --> 14:47.051
Do you want some
unsolicited advice?

14:48.388 --> 14:50.388
Don't try anything
on the first date.

14:51.524 --> 14:53.391
A woman
likes to be romanced.

14:54.794 --> 14:57.462
A gentleman saves that stuff
for the second date.

14:58.732 --> 14:59.997
And on our third date,

15:01.200 --> 15:03.801
Your grandmother
told me she was pregnant!

15:03.870 --> 15:05.069
Huh?!

15:05.138 --> 15:06.870
Good night.

15:06.907 --> 15:08.273
[melancholy music]

15:09.342 --> 15:10.874
[coughing resumes]

15:22.222 --> 15:23.087
<i> - I had a date!</i>

15:23.156 --> 15:26.524
<i> That is, if I could only</i>
<i> get to it.</i>

15:28.094 --> 15:30.361
- How come
you're all dressed up?

15:32.766 --> 15:33.231
You got a date!

15:33.233 --> 15:35.433
Can I come?

15:35.568 --> 15:36.900
- No!

15:37.570 --> 15:39.036
Where's victoria park?

15:39.105 --> 15:40.838
I think I've got to get
the route 2?

15:40.840 --> 15:43.174
- No, you take the route 3
then transfer at parade street.

15:43.243 --> 15:45.510
- Where's that?

15:45.645 --> 15:47.745
- You sure
you don't want me to come?

15:47.880 --> 15:50.848
- Okay, but promise you won't
follow us and be weird?

15:50.984 --> 15:51.982
- I promise.

15:52.018 --> 15:53.317
I'll just watch you
guys from the bushes --

15:53.353 --> 15:54.818
No weird stuff.

15:55.588 --> 15:56.921
- Okay.

15:57.056 --> 15:58.389
Cool.

16:00.060 --> 16:01.259
[bus brakes squeal
and hiss]

16:03.930 --> 16:05.129
- Ritchie:
Can we get

16:05.131 --> 16:06.931
Two transfers,
please?

16:07.066 --> 16:08.199
[coins clinking
in fare box]

16:09.803 --> 16:10.935
[bus doors close]

16:11.070 --> 16:12.269
- Hey, dicks.

16:12.305 --> 16:14.338
- Oh, hi, fox!
We've got a date!

16:14.374 --> 16:16.541
- What?
- Uh, not with each other.

16:16.676 --> 16:17.342
With a girl.

16:17.477 --> 16:19.176
- Shut up! Shut up!
Shut up!

16:20.413 --> 16:23.214
- Well, he has a girl,
I don't.

16:23.349 --> 16:25.149
You're a girl,
so maybe we can double-date?

16:25.284 --> 16:27.518
- [scoffs]
- ow!

16:27.587 --> 16:29.153
- What girl?
- He doesn't know her name.

16:29.222 --> 16:31.688
- My god,
yes, I do!

16:31.725 --> 16:32.923
It's nothing!

16:34.427 --> 16:36.728
- Hey, driver,
I want a transfer, too.

16:39.933 --> 16:41.098
- Ohh...
- [thudding]

16:41.134 --> 16:42.767
[exciting music]

17:03.890 --> 17:05.189
- Hey.

17:05.258 --> 17:06.723
- Hey.

17:08.161 --> 17:10.061
- So, come here often?

17:13.666 --> 17:15.933
["everything in my heart"
by corey hart plays]

17:25.311 --> 17:28.746
<i> ♪♪ I never</i>
<i> see the light ♪♪</i>

17:30.216 --> 17:33.151
<i>- Her hands were as soft as the</i>
<i>most expensive toilet paper</i>

17:33.153 --> 17:34.518
<i> At the supermarket.</i>

17:35.422 --> 17:37.154
<i> They were almost</i>
<i> as soft as mine.</i>

17:38.058 --> 17:40.091
<i> ♪♪ couldn't imagine how ♪♪</i>

17:41.361 --> 17:44.027
<i> ♪♪ what I'm</i>
<i> supposed to do ♪♪</i>

17:44.831 --> 17:45.362
- [crack]
- ow!!

17:45.398 --> 17:47.698
Uncle!
Uncle!

17:49.368 --> 17:51.201
I'll call you!

17:52.705 --> 17:54.805
<i> ♪♪ only thinking</i>
<i> of you ♪♪</i>

17:56.909 --> 17:58.609
<i> ♪♪ I'll do it</i>
<i> again ♪♪</i>

18:00.146 --> 18:01.378
- I gotta go.

18:01.815 --> 18:03.648
[smack]

18:03.783 --> 18:05.916
<i> ♪♪ everything</i>
<i> in my heart ♪♪</i>

18:05.985 --> 18:07.384
<i> - My second kiss!</i>

18:07.386 --> 18:08.819
<i> At this rate,</i>

18:08.822 --> 18:10.954
<i> I'd be married</i>
<i> by my 13th birthday.</i>

18:13.926 --> 18:15.126
- Nice work.

18:15.261 --> 18:16.794
- Wanna go
down the slide?

18:16.929 --> 18:18.195
- Race ya'!

18:21.868 --> 18:23.200
[phone ringing]

18:24.270 --> 18:26.737
- Good god!

18:26.773 --> 18:28.606
Who's calling the house
at this hour?

18:28.608 --> 18:30.408
It's half past seven
at night!

18:30.410 --> 18:31.943
- I'll get it!

18:33.012 --> 18:33.410
Hello?

18:33.446 --> 18:35.379
<i> - Hi.</i>

18:35.448 --> 18:36.447
It's tina,
the hussy.

18:36.449 --> 18:39.283
- That was amazing. I--

18:39.352 --> 18:41.119
- I'm breaking up
with you.

18:42.088 --> 18:43.487
- What?
Why?

18:43.556 --> 18:44.888
<i> - I don't know.</i>

18:44.924 --> 18:46.256
'cuz you're slack.

18:47.093 --> 18:47.558
- Slack?

18:47.560 --> 18:49.360
What's slack?

18:49.429 --> 18:51.462
- She means
you didn't put out, son.

18:51.597 --> 18:52.296
Oh, that's my fault.

18:52.431 --> 18:54.632
Tell her
about the second date!

18:54.701 --> 18:56.099
<i> - Slack?</i>

18:56.136 --> 18:59.036
<i> Sister rose was right:</i>
<i> We were too young for this.</i>

19:00.073 --> 19:01.438
- Can't we just--

19:01.474 --> 19:04.208
[pebbles hitting window]

19:04.210 --> 19:05.510
- Hang on.

19:13.353 --> 19:14.652
Just leave me alone!

19:18.491 --> 19:19.390
[handset onto cradle]

19:19.459 --> 19:21.992
[dial tone]

19:24.464 --> 19:25.329
[dial tone continues]

19:25.331 --> 19:27.532
[handset onto cradle]

19:27.667 --> 19:28.466
- That brazen
little hussy.

19:28.601 --> 19:31.135
Oh, she better not
call here anymore!

19:31.270 --> 19:32.803
You know, her father's
nowhere to be found.

19:32.939 --> 19:33.537
I talked to joan
down at the supermarket

19:33.540 --> 19:35.872
And she told me that--

19:35.909 --> 19:37.241
- No, no, no.

19:37.744 --> 19:39.744
[door slams]

19:39.879 --> 19:41.212
- Oh, mm.

19:41.981 --> 19:42.346
I've got it.

19:42.481 --> 19:44.781
[door opens]

19:45.451 --> 19:47.050
[door closes]

19:52.425 --> 19:53.890
[aluminum foil crinkling]

19:54.427 --> 19:56.760
[pop groans]

19:56.829 --> 19:59.162
Yeah, little surprise
for ya'.

19:59.832 --> 20:00.297
Hm?

20:00.366 --> 20:02.567
Ham and cheese.

20:03.336 --> 20:04.334
Nice.

20:04.370 --> 20:06.971
Mm.

20:06.973 --> 20:07.504
Come on!

20:07.540 --> 20:09.906
How was your date?

20:09.943 --> 20:12.109
- I guess
I'm not ready yet.

20:12.245 --> 20:12.643
- Oh...

20:12.679 --> 20:14.912
Don't worry.

20:15.047 --> 20:15.712
You will be.

20:15.748 --> 20:17.715
Women are
what they call...

20:18.384 --> 20:19.916
An acquired taste.

20:20.820 --> 20:23.254
- Like stale
funeral sandwiches?

20:23.323 --> 20:25.389
- Ah, christ, no!

20:25.825 --> 20:28.059
No.

20:29.328 --> 20:30.461
I wish I could tell you
that it doesn't matter,

20:30.530 --> 20:32.095
That you'll
forget her.

20:33.299 --> 20:34.598
The truth is...

20:35.902 --> 20:38.602
You'll always remember
the first one.

20:40.974 --> 20:42.206
And the last.

20:42.208 --> 20:43.007
Hm.

20:43.076 --> 20:44.942
It's just the ones
in the middle

20:45.011 --> 20:47.278
That don't seem to matter
all that much.

20:47.347 --> 20:51.281
You just try and squeeze in
as many of those as you can.

20:51.317 --> 20:52.783
[upbeat music]

20:53.686 --> 20:55.119
<i> - Sitting there</i>
<i> on my bed</i>

20:55.254 --> 20:57.755
<i> As pop and I polished off</i>
<i> the funeral sandwiches,</i>

20:57.757 --> 20:59.423
<i> I learned two things:</i>

20:59.425 --> 21:01.592
<i> One, you can't</i>
<i> hurry love.</i>

21:01.594 --> 21:02.960
<i> And, two,</i>

21:03.029 --> 21:05.563
<i> The pain of heartache</i>
<i> is no match for heartburn.</i>

21:05.565 --> 21:07.164
[pop sighs]

21:08.167 --> 21:08.565
- Ach.

21:08.635 --> 21:11.001
[pop groans]

21:11.637 --> 21:12.636
- Good night.

21:12.672 --> 21:14.237
- Good night, pop.

21:18.044 --> 21:18.509
[pop coughing]

21:18.578 --> 21:20.978
♪♪

21:21.648 --> 21:22.979
- Pop:
Oh, jesus!
